  <h1>
   audio_sound_get_pitch
  </h1>
  This function can be used to get the get pitch of a given sound. The sound can either be one referenced from an index for an individual sound being played which has been stored in a variable when using the
  <a href="audio_play_sound.htm">
   <span>
    audio_play_sound()
   </span>
  </a>
  or
  <a href="audio_play_sound_at.htm">
   <span>
    audio_play_sound_at()
   </span>
  </a>
  functions, or an actual sound asset from the Asset Browser.
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">audio_sound_get_pitch(index);
</code></pre>
  <table>
   <tbody>
    <tr>
     <th>
      Argument
     </th>
     <th>
      Type
     </th>
     <th>
      Description
     </th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      index
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../The_Asset_Editors/Sounds.htm">
        Sound Asset
       </a>
      </span>
      or
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Reference/Asset_Management/Audio/audio_play_sound.htm">
        Sound Instance ID
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The index of the sound to get the pitch of.
     </td>
    </tr>
   </tbody>
  </table>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml"><a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
 Real
</a></code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">if audio_sound_get_pitch(snd_Explode) != 1
{
    audio_sound_pitch(snd_Explode, 1);
}
</code></pre>
  The above code will change the pitch of the audio played from the sound indexed as "snd_Explode" if its pitch is not equal to 1.
